Date: 09-09-2025 & 16-09-2025


Aim
To compute factorial of a non-negative integer using recursion.
To throw IllegalArgumentException if input is negative.
To handle invalid integer inputs via InputMismatchException.
Algorithm
Read an integer N using Scanner.
If N < 0, throw IllegalArgumentException with given message.
Else compute factorial recursively: f(0)=1; f(n)=n×f(n−1).
Print the factorial value.
Catch InputMismatchException and print given message.
Catch IllegalArgumentException and print its message.
End program.
Program (Java)
import java.util.*;
public class SafeFactorial {
    static long fact(int n){
        if (n == 0) return 1;
        return n * fact(n - 1);
    }
    public static void main(String[] args){
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        try {
            int n = sc.nextInt();
            if (n < 0) throw new IllegalArgumentException("Error: Input must be non-negative");
            System.out.println(fact(n));
        } catch (InputMismatchException e){
            System.out.println("Error: Input must be a valid integer.");
        } catch (IllegalArgumentException e){
            System.out.println(e.getMessage());
        } finally {
            sc.close();
        }
    }
}


Sample Output
Input: 5
Output: 120
Result
Handled both invalid type and negative value inputs gracefully.
Produced correct factorial for valid non-negative input.
